snippet.title: NRL Late Mail: Walker, Burgess cleared
snippet.content:
NRL Late Mail heading into round 22. * Under-fire Canterbury coach Des Hasler has overhauled his team, with Chase Stanley to play in the halves alongside Josh Reynolds and Brenko Lee to play centre; * Tepai Moeroa is out through injury for the Eels; * Sam Burgess (rib cartilage), Adam Reynolds (concussion/jaw) and Angus Crichton (foot) are certain starters for the Rabbitohs; * Corey Oates (staph infection) is expected to be a late inclusion for the Broncos; * Dylan Walker (ankle/foot) is considered a certain starter for the Sea Eagles; * Fa'manu Brown (concussion) has been cleared despite a sickening head knock last week. Adam Elliott 13. David Klemmer. Interchange: 14. Sam Kasiano 15. Raymond Faitala-Mariner 16. Danny Fualalo 17. Michael Lichaa 19. Francis Tualau 20. Kerrod Holland 21. Asipeli Fine 23. Brenko Lee Players cut: Kerrod Holland, Asipeli Fine Late mail: Des Hasler has pulled a host of surprises. Chase Stanley shifts to the halves alongside Josh Reynolds, with Brenko Lee to fill Stanley's right centre position. Either Matt Frawley or Michael Lichaa drops back to NSW Cup. Sam Kasiano (sternum) and Adam Elliott (knock) have been cleared. Eels: 1. Bevan French 2. Semi Radradra 3. Michael Jennings 4. Brad Takairangi 5. Kirisome Auva'a 6. Corey Norman 7. Mitchell Moses 8. Kyle Turner 17. Cameron Murray 18. Anthony Cherrington 19. Jack Gosiewski 20. David Tyrrell 22. Campbell Graham Players cut: To come Late mail: "Sam will be out there with Adam, doing what they normally do with all of the younger guys coming through and it's about getting out and getting a really strong performance," coach Michael Maguire said. "Angus and Sam are actually improving. Every player trains to play, and these boys are no different. Players run around all week and do what they do because they enjoy stepping out on to the park and playing football. There's never been a discussion about them not wanting to play. Sam could have gone back on last week, and he wanted to go back on, but I made the call, and it was an opportunity to give someone else a run. And Angus is coming out the other end with his bumps and bruises. Sam's leadership has grown this year, and Angus has really grown under Sam.'' Cowboys v Storm
